                        <r3d:remarks>Data from the British Household Panel Study have been deposited in the UK Data Archive, from whom data access can be granted.  Access to the  data of UK Data Archive is via registration on the ESDS site and agreement to an End User Licence. A few datasets are subject to special conditions of access, and others require a special licence before they can be used. //  UK.Data Archive is covered by Thomson Reuters Data Citation Index.
Offering and depositing your data to the Archive are simple processes. We review all offers of data and guide you through the deposit process. Depositing involves preparing your data with our guidance and completing the accompanying forms. 
Since its establishment over 40 years ago the UK Data Archive has acquired, preserved and managed a vast range of data. We acquire data from academic, public sector and commercial sources within the United Kingdom and abroad. Since 2005 our Archive has been designated a Place of Deposit by The National Archives. We are part of the pan-European CESSDA ERIC Catalogue. From there you can locate data and variables from selected data collections stored at a number of European social science data archives. We also hold several key international survey series which can be found in our DataCatalogue.</r3d:remarks>
